From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pantavisor <dev@pantavisor.io>
Date: Mon, 24 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: imx8mn-var-som-m7: fix remoteproc for Linux
 start

Fix two issues preventing the M7 core from being started via Linux
remoteproc:

1. Switch from SMC to MMIO method (fsl,imx8mn-cm7-mmio). The SMC
   method calls into ATF which may not implement SIP_RPROC on all
   boards. MMIO uses the GPR22 register directly, matching U-Boot's
   bootaux mechanism. Add required syscon and fsl,iomuxc-gpr phandles.

2. Reference the actual M7 core clock (IMX8MN_CLK_M7_CORE) instead
   of CLK_DUMMY. Without this, Linux's clock framework gates the M7
   clock during boot, causing a hard hang when remoteproc tries to
   access M7 memory or start the core.

Signed-off-by: Pantavisor <dev@pantavisor.io>
---
 .../freescale/imx8mn-var-som-symphony-m7.dts  | 6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/imx8mn-var-som-symphony-m7.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/imx8mn-var-som-symphony-m7.dts
index abcdef1..1234567 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/imx8mn-var-som-symphony-m7.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/imx8mn-var-som-symphony-m7.dts
@@ -10,8 +10,10 @@
 	model = "Variscite VAR-SOM-MX8M-NANO M7 on Symphony-Board";

 	imx8mn-cm7 {
-		compatible = "fsl,imx8mn-cm7";
-		rsc-da = <0x40000000>;
+		compatible = "fsl,imx8mn-cm7-mmio";
+		syscon = <&src>;
+		fsl,iomuxc-gpr = <&gpr>;
+		rsc-da = <0x40000000>;
 		clocks = <&clk IMX8MN_CLK_M7_CORE>;
 		mbox-names = "tx", "rx", "rxdb";
